                            <comment id="13490480" author="fmeschbe" created="Mon, 5 Nov 2012 06:59:24 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;Is this a release blocker ?&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;On the implementation: This looks tricky because the properties are updated in the createImplementationObject and disposeImplementationObject methods, resp., while the fields are set in the callers &amp;#8211; and not all callers to the same handling.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;Now, the disposeImplementationObject method could just return the service properties to be set. But the createImplementationObject returns the service object and so cannot easily return the properties.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;One option would be to enhance the MethodResult object with the component reference and the methods return MethodResult. This would convey all we need but isn&apos;t this breaching some encapsulation barrier ? (Though it remains in the same classe)&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="13491942" author="djencks" created="Tue, 6 Nov 2012 23:20:58 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;r1406395  This is easy to fix and IMO a release blocker.&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="13501051" author="fmeschbe" created="Tue, 20 Nov 2012 10:58:17 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;Close after release&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
